i have a story, for anyone that wants to hear it. this is about my best friend and massive lifelong crush.

let's call my friend "H".

so, we met in 2nd grade when she moved to my school (in Kentucky) from Hawaii. at the time i had a different friend, let's call her "C". so, me and C had been friends since kindergarten. i knew that C was going to go into homeschooling at the end of the year, so i was feeling really sad and tried to make some new friends. at first i hated H because i thought she was trying to steal C from me. but after a while me, C, and H became a group. as it neared the end of the year, i met this random boy, we will call him "B". so, when i met B i didn't know what to think because i had only had female friends before this. i started to develop feelings for B. B didn't like my other friends, so i wasn't sure how to feel or what to do since i had to choose between B (who i fell really hard for), or C and H. it was the end of second grade, and me and H said our last goodbyes to C. we never saw C again. in 3rd grade, ms and H were in different classes. me and B were in the same class again. me and B had other friends (which aren't important enough to name.) and at this point i had H, and me and B's friend group. B hated H. i ended up telling H about my feelings for B. then i told a few other people. as expected, B found out. In comparision to that boys should be strong, not show many emotions, wear pants, have short hair etc. . 
The sentence "I wish I were heather" could be conan¬¥s wish of getting out of these norms. that boys wearing dresses and skirts should be normalized. To normalize boys having long hair and not telling them that that¬¥s a "girly" thing.

thank you for coming to my ted talk ^^
